<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!--
   Bebecup full-backup rules.

   Bebecup keeps all data on-device (Room DB at <internal>/databases/ and the
   user-selected photo URIs referenced from it). There is no analytics, ad,
   or external sync component, so no data needs to be excluded from Google
   Auto Backup for privacy reasons.

   The Room database is included implicitly. Photo URIs may not resolve on a
   restored device because they are device-local persisted Photo Picker grants
   — that limitation is by design (re-pick the source photos on the new
   device) and is documented in docs/PRIVACY_POLICY_DRAFT.md.

   See https://developer.android.com/guide/topics/data/autobackup for details.
   Pre-API-31 devices read these rules; API 31+ uses data_extraction_rules.xml.
-->
<full-backup-content />
